article.headline: Smith, Quigley score 23 each in DePaul rout
article.story:
MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Khara Smith and Allie Quigley each scored 23
points to lead No. 14 DePaul to a 91-79 victory over
Wisconsin-Milwaukee on Wednesday night.
	   Erin Carney, Jenna Rubino and Erin Cattell each scored 11 points
for the Blue Demons, who improved to 6-0. Smith added a game-best
16 rebounds for DePaul, which won its 550th game, against 331
losses, in 32 seasons.
	   Traci Edwards scored 21 points for the Panthers (2-3). Nichole
Drummond added 20 points and Molly O'Brien 14. The Panthers are
winless in three games against the Blue Demons.
	   After a number of lead changes in the opening minutes of the
second half, Missy Mitidiero hit a 3-pointer to put DePaul ahead
for good at 48-45. Milwaukee quickly pulled within a point on a
pair of free throws by Turquoise McCain. But Quigley, who scored 20
points in the half, responded with a basket and 3-pointer to push
the lead to 53-47. The Panthers never got that close again.
	   Smith scored with 5 seconds left in the first half to give
DePaul its first lead of the game at 37-36.
	   The Panthers led 19-10 with 13:58 left after a 3-pointer by
O'Brien. But the Blue Demons, sparked by nine points from Cattell,
a reserve, and 10 from Smith, rallied and caught the Panthers at
the end of the period.
